article.headline: Kent State 70, Buffalo 52
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Kevin Warzynski scored 19 points lead Kent State to a 70-52 win over Buffalo on Sunday. Kent (14-6, 8-1 Mid-American Conference) put the game away early, going on a 29-10 run in the first half. Jay Youngblood scored 14 points and Omni Smith added 10 for Kent, which shot 46.8 percent for the game (29-of-62) and was coming off its first conference loss of the season, a 79-74 defeat Thursday against Bowling Green. Yassin Idbihi led Buffalo (15-5, 5-4) with 16 points. Calvin Cage added 11. The loss snapped a two-game winning streak. Buffalo shot 34 percent (17-of-50).
